  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Transforming Teaching and Learning at Schools for Achieving SGD4: turning theory into practice with ICT</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The joint Project is aimed at supporting the promotion of the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), recognizing and encouraging excellence with the use of technology in schools through curriculum design, group work, seminars, projects and global interaction, teacher development and training, collection, analysis and dissemination of best practices.
Key Project priorities:
1.	To enrich educational process and experience exchange around SDG&apos;s values and priorities.
2.	Develop and disseminate best practices on ICT competencies of schools.
3.	Promote networking and collaboration among targeted schools to meet the challenges and commitments of the interrelated SDGs.</narrative>
  </description>
